# Copy to `.env.local` (Next.js loads it automatically; never commit `.env.local`).
#
# Ollama must be reachable from the SAME machine that runs `npm run dev`.
# - Same PC as Ollama: use loopback (IPv4 avoids resolver delay):
OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:11434
#
# - Next.js on spiritdesktop, Ollama on another host (e.g. Dell / Node 2):
#   1) On the Ollama host: `ip addr` → note LAN IP
#   2) From the Next.js host: `curl -s http://127.0.0.1:11434/api/tags | head -c 100`
#      JSON → Ollama is local. "Connection refused" → set LAN IP here instead:
# OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://192.168.x.x:11434
#
# Docker: ensure the stack is up, e.g. `cd ../backend && docker compose up -d ollama`
# Model: `docker exec spirit-ollama ollama list` should include dolphin3
